Description
Character
Class-Description:
Abstract class for all characters providing methods for name matching and updating.
The Character-Class implements the Serializable-Interface.
CharacterContainer
Class-Description:
Container for created characters with basic CRUD functionality Implemented as singleton and Serializable to save the data on a hard drive.
CharacterController
Class-Description:
Spring rest controller providing URLs for CRUD operations on the character container.
CharacterNotFound
Class-Description:
Exception for spring rest service if a character was not found.
HomeController
Class-Description:
Controller for serving index.html
LordOfRingsChar
Class-Description:
The class "LordOfRingsChar" is a concrete child class of the abstract Character and represents Characters from the LotR-Universe.
ProjectApplication
Class-Description:
Entry Point for application Start tomcat server with Rest-Api and serving frontend as single index.html Server hosted on http://localhost:8080/
Serializer
Class-Description:
The Serializer-Class contains methods to write to and read a file.
StarWarsChar
Class-Description:
The class "StarWarsChar" is a concrete child class of the abstract Character and represents Characters from the Star-Wars-Universe.
UpdateVisitor
Class-Description:
The UpdateVisitor-Class automatically differentiate between the two concrete classes and perfomes the updateprocess of these classes.
